    {
      "scene_id": "scene_001",
      "scene_number": 1,
      "text": "INT. SMALL APARTMENT KITCHEN - DAY\n\n[Approx. Timestamp: 00:00:00]\nThe kitchen is tiny, cluttered with half-prepped food, pots bubbling, and a giant \"CATERING GIG TODAY\" sticky note on the fridge. JAKE (28, enthusiastic but perpetually overwhelmed amateur chef) wears a stained apron that says \"Kiss the Cook... or Run.\" His best friend and reluctant business partner, MIA (27, sarcastic, always one eye-roll away from quitting), chops vegetables like she's angry at them.\n\nJAKE\n(excited, waving a ladle)\nThis is it, Mia! Our first real catering job. Fifty people at the tech startup launch party. We're gonna crush it. Gourmet sliders, mini quiches, that fancy charcuterie thing you saw on TikTok\u2014\n\nMIA\n(deadpan)\nThe one where everything looks perfect and then someone drops it on the floor? Yeah, we're nailing that vibe already.\n\nA smoke alarm suddenly BLARES. Jake rushes to the oven, yanks out a tray of blackened mini quiches.\n\nJAKE\nNo, no, no! They're... extra crispy! Trendy!\n\nMIA\nThey're charcoal briquettes with cheese. We're doomed.\n\nJake's phone BUZZES. He answers on speaker.\n\nJAKE\nHey, Mr. Patel! Yes, we're on schedule. Everything's under control\u2014\n\nMR. PATEL (O.S., frantic)\nJake! Change of plans! The venue flooded. We're moving it here\u2014to my apartment! Right now! And... we adopted a cat last week. Super friendly. Loves people. Bring extra food!\n\nClick. Silence.\n\nMIA\nA cat. In a tiny apartment. With fifty tech bros. And our food.\n\nJAKE\nIt's fine. Cats love sliders. We'll improvise.",
