    {
      "scene_id": "scene_003",
      "scene_number": 3,
      "text": "INT. KITCHENETTE - CONTINUOUS\n\n[Approx. Timestamp: 00:06:00]\nMia and Jake retreat to regroup. Mr. Patel bursts in, holding the cat like a football.\n\nMR. PATEL\nHe's just excited! New people! New smells!\n\nThe cat wriggles free, dashes out.\n\nJAKE\nWe need a plan. Mia, distract the guests with... charm?\n\nMIA\nCharm? I have resting murder face. You distract. I'll salvage what food we have left.\n\nJake nods, grabs a microphone (it's a karaoke setup for the party).\n\nJAKE\n(into mic, too loud)\nHey everyone! Welcome! I'm Jake, your chef tonight. Quick story: I once burned water. True story. But tonight? Tonight we're elevating!\n\nGuests chuckle. Sir Whiskers reappears, leaps onto Jake's shoulder like a pirate parrot.\n\nJAKE\n(trying to play it cool)\nAnd this is Sir Whiskers, our... official taste-tester!\n\nThe cat bats at the mic cord. It tangles around Jake's legs. He stumbles, knocks over a stack of chairs. Domino effect\u2014chairs topple, a table flips, charcuterie rains down like confetti.\n\nGuests scream-laugh. Phones come out\u2014video time.\n\nMIA\n(running in)\nJake!\n\nShe grabs a broom, tries to herd the cat. Instead, she sweeps Jake's feet out. He falls backward into a pile of cushions, cat landing on his chest purring.\n\nJAKE\n(from the floor, defeated but grinning)\nAppetizers are served... floor-style.\n\nThe room erupts in applause and laughter. Someone starts a slow clap. Others join.\n\nGUEST #3\nThis is the best launch party ever! Way better than free pizza!\n\nMR. PATEL\n(tearful, happy)\nYou guys... you turned disaster into legend!\n\nMia helps Jake up. The cat rubs against her leg.\n\nMIA\n(softening, smirking)\nOkay, fine. We're not fired. Yet.\n\nJAKE\nNext gig: Cat-proof everything.\n\nThey high-five. Sir Whiskers meows triumphantly.\n\nGuests swarm the spilled food\u2014picking it up, eating anyway, toasting \"to chaos!\"",
